 four points: the Sinai covenant according to Exodus, the reenactment of that covenant according to Deuteronomy, the call for a NEW covenant according to Jeremiah, and the present reality of that covenant established by God and mediated by Jesus Christ.The basis for Hebrews' critique arises from its insight that while Israel's request established covenant-from-a-distance, Jesus demonstrates that true covenant mediation brings two parties into a single space. The purpose for Hebrews critique lies in its summons to Zion, the mountain on which Jesus sits at the right hand of God as the high priestly mediator of the new covenant.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCovenantsxBiblical teaching. 0aFailure (Psychology)xBiblical teaching. 0aFearxBiblical teaching. 0aIsrael (Christian theology)xBiblical teaching. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Paul's Letters.2bisacsh  aHebrews.  aMoses.  aSinai.  aZion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104227640 cprintz978311042657140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042259740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110422597423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110422597/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL